  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agbogbloshie Development Project (ADP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For tens of thousands of people living in Agbogbloshie, a large slum area in Accra, living conditions are squalid. As well as the usual problems of overcrowding, poor quality housing, lack of sanitation and constant threat of eviction, the area is also a dump for industrial waste. This project aims to improve the quality of life for people living in the slum, particularly women and youth, by mobilising slum dwellers and the government to improve conditions. People will receive practical training so they can earn money. Local groups will be formed to negotiate better housing and take part in community improvements. The project will work with community leaders, the local authority and government departments to engage them on housing, environmental and health issues. As a result, some people will be able to move out of the slum and others will be able to increase their income and improve their living conditions, as part of a bigger push for urban regeneration.</narrative>
  </description>
